thread.title: Spotify's Top 10 most viral tracks
thread.title_full: Spotify's Top 10 most viral tracks - Yahoo News

author: The Associated Press
title: Spotify's Top 10 most viral tracks
text:
The following list represents the most viral tracks on Spotify, based on the number of people who shared it divided by the number who listened to it, from Friday Oct. 2, to Thursday, Oct. 8, via Facebook, Tumblr, Twitter and Spotify.
UNITED STATES
1. DNCE, "Cake By The Ocean" (Republic Records)
2. Louis The Child, K.Flay, "It's Strange (feat. K.Flay)" (Next Wave Records)
3. Leslie Odom Jr., Anthony Ramos, Daveed Diggs, Okieriete Onaodowan, Lin-Manuel Miranda, Christopher Jackson, Phillipa Soo, Original Broadway Cast of Hamilton, "Alexander Hamilton" (Atlantic / WEA)
4. Gnash, Olivia O'Brien, "I Hate U I Love U (feat. Olivia O'Brien)" (Gnash)
5. Lady Leshurr, "Queen's Speech 4" (Lady Leshurr)
6. Stephen, "Fly Down" (Halfway House)
7. Tyler Ward, Two Worlds, "Watch Me (Whip / Nae Nae) - Acoustic" (mudhutdigital.com)
8. Emmi, "Sleep On It" (Emmi Music)
9. Tate Kobang, "Bank Rolls - Remix" (300 Entertainment)
10. GRADES, "King" (Warner Music UK Limited)
UNITED KINGDOM
1. WSTRN, "In2" (Atlantic Records UK)
2. KDA, Tinie Tempah, Katy B, "Turn The Music Louder (Rumble) - Radio Edit" (Ministry of Sound Recordings Ltd.)
3. Joe Gilgun, Vicky McClure, Chanel Cresswell, Danielle Watson, "Wanky Shank" (UMC (Universal Music Catalogue))
4. Toydrum, Gavin Clark, "I've Got A Future" (Underscore Collective)
5. The Lake Poets, "Edinburgh" (Membran Rights Management Ltd.)
6. Jamie Lawson, "Wasn't Expecting That" (Ginberbread Man Records)
7. Bxnjamin, Chanele McGuinness, "Moon River - A Duet" (Nowever Records)
8. DNCE, "Cake By The Ocean" (Republic Records)
9. Sensible Soccers, "AFG" (Groovement Organic Series)
10. EODM (Eagles Of Death Metal), "Save A Prayer" (Universal Music Entertprises)
GLOBAL
1. DNCE, "Cake By The Ocean" (Republic Records)
2. Louis The Child, K.Flay, "It's Strange (feat. K.Flay)" (Next Wave Records)
3. Gnash, Olivia O'Brien, "I Hate U I Love U (feat. Olivia O'Brien)" (Gnash)
4. Leslie Odom Jr., Anthony Ramos, Daveed Diggs, Okieriete Onaodowan, Lin-Manuel Miranda, Christopher Jackson, Phillipa Soo, Original Broadway Cast of Hamilton, "Alexander Hamilton" (Atlantic / WEA)
5. Stephen, "Fly Down" (Halfway House)
6. Rebel, Sophie Simmons, "Kiss Me" (Republic Records)
7. Emmi, "Sleep On It" (Emmi Music)
8. Tate Kobang, "Bank Rolls - Remix" (300 Entertainment)
9. Lady Leshurr, "Queen's Speech 4" (Lady Leshurr)
10. Rudimental, Ed Sheeran, "Lay It All On Me (feat. Ed Sheeran)" (Asylum Records UK)
